<L>__{exterior courthouse steps dusk}
<A>__{alone on the steps where the strawberry princess once winked at him. snow has begun to fall, soft and altogether beautiful. he squints up...}
<C>__{ishmael }
<D>__{god's kindness, my father said. despite the hardship...it reminds us. of our place in things.}
<A>__{our place in things. he slides a black cigar between his teeth...}
<C>__{ishmael }
<D>__{what the hell. did he mean by that?}
<A>__{he has the match box. manipulating it with the dexterity we've come to know.}
<C>__{ishmael }
<D>__{things fall on us, i suppose. from the sky.}
<A>__{strikes the match on his belt buckle...}
<C>__{ishmael }
<D>__{wars. freighters plowing through...}
<A>__{cupping it expertly in a single motion, he brings the flame to the cigar. a single puff.}
<C>__{ishmael }
